definition:
A woman of the tribe of Levi living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Exo.6.20; 
 daughter of: Levi (H3878); 
 sister of: Gershon (H1648), Kohath (H6955) and Merari (H4847); married to Amram (H6019); 
 mother of: Moses (H4872), Aaron (H0175) and Miriam (H4813) 
 § Jochebed = "Jehovah is glory"
 the daughter of Levi, wife and at the same time aunt of Amram, and the mother of Moses, Aaron, and Miriam
